  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db1\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d94\u0dba\u0dda \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The bodies of the elk are floating in Nanu Oi",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The bodies of a large number of elk roaming in the Hortonthanna Reserve are floating in the Nanuoya Ambewela Reservoir, according to the conservationists who are engaged in the conservation activities of the reservoir.",
        "Dhiwarain said that about ten elks die in the reservoir a week.",
        "A few hunters in the Ambewela area have trained and abandoned many dogs that bite the elk coming from Horton to find food and water and chase them into the reservoir. Says",
        "Dhiwarain claims that the bodies of many well-grown elk are currently floating on the Ambewela Reservoir, and due to the current situation, the environment of the reservoir has also been destroyed.",
        "The water released from Ambewela Reservoir is being used for drinking water and cultivation purposes in Welimada Rendapola and Talawakele area, and although the wildlife officers have been informed about this, the officers have not taken any action for this, according to the workers who are engaged in the excavation work of Ambewela Reservoir.",
        "Due to the current situation, there is a strong stench in the reservoir, and the owners of the Ambewela reservoir are asking the wildlife officials to take necessary steps to catch the dogs that hunt and kill the elk and take them to another area immediately."
      ],
